 To add a column element to each task, you can do the following:

1. Extract the column name as you have already done.

2. Add a columnName property to each task object:

```js
taskCard.columnName = columnName;
```

3. When logging the task details, also log the column name:

```js
console.log(`Date: ${date}, Task Description: ${taskDescription}, Badges: ${badges}, Assigned Person: ${assignedPerson}, Column: ${taskCard.columnName}`);  
```

The full code would be:
```js
// Get column name 
let columnName = document.querySelector('h3.m-2.p-2').innerText;

// Get task cards 
let taskCards = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('div\[data-name="task-card"\]'));

taskCards.forEach((taskCard) => {
  // Add column name to task object
  taskCard.columnName = columnName;

  // Extract date 
  let dateElement = taskCard.querySelector('p.text-muted.fw-bold.d-block.m-2'); 
  let date = dateElement ? dateElement.innerText : "No date provided";

  // Extract task title and description 
  let taskDescriptionElement = taskCard.querySelector('p.white-space-normal.text-truncate-3-lines.max-h-90px');
  let taskDescription = taskDescriptionElement ? taskDescriptionElement.innerText : "No task description provided";

  // Extract badges
  let badges = Array.from(taskCard.querySelectorAll('.badge')).map(badge => badge.innerText);
  badges = badges.length > 0 ? badges : \["No badges"\];

  // Extract assigned person 
  let assignedPersonElement = taskCard.querySelector('.sb-avatar__image');
  let assignedPerson = assignedPersonElement ? assignedPersonElement.alt : "No person assigned";

  console.log(\`Date: ${date}, Task Description: ${taskDescription}, Badges: ${badges}, Assigned Person: ${assignedPerson}, Column: ${taskCard.columnName}\`); 
});
```

Hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.

